{
  "stem": "1062.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "The woman, most of them, were dressed in white.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Everybody in the family was in shul.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "Some of the man stayed in shul all night long until Yom Kippur was over.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] There was one time when I went to the rabbi.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "Well, see, my village was a small village.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "But a lot of people used to go to the rebbe.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And I remember once, me and my father, we went down to the Spinka Rebbe for Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "It was a big thing for the Hasidic-- I wouldn't say we were Hasidic.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "But over there, everybody belonged to a rabbi.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "This rebbe, by the way, was not only a rebbe, a teacher.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "He was also a miracle maker.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "If you had a problem in business, in business, you went to the rebbe.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "You were sick, you went to the rebbe.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "I remember my father once-- it's just a thought which I have right now-- he went to the rebbe, you know, because he was a farmer.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "And-- and-- and when he brought in things from the-- from the farm, was-- it was-- there was hardly anything-- anything-- you know, the-- it was a very poor harvest.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "And my father was-- we had six children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he went to the rebbe.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he asked the rebbe what to do because he wouldn't have enough bread for the children.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the rebbe told him to buy two sheep because he told him, from sheep, you get wool, you get milk, you could get meat.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And sheep is going to be a blessing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he bought two sheeps.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He borrowed money.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He bought two sheep.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think about-- took about three, four months, and the two sheep died.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
